Folley Cove simply calls her "Jinnee."

00:13:29.930 --> 00:13:36.290
Anyone who meets Jinnee will tell you that
she is quite magical.

00:13:36.290 --> 00:13:42.480
[pause] She makes things grow in an enchanted
garden.

00:13:42.480 --> 00:13:45.130
She talks to the chickens and the sheep.

00:13:45.130 --> 00:13:47.380
And even the little pit mouse.

00:13:47.380 --> 00:13:53.019
And, of course, they share all their secrets.

00:13:53.019 --> 00:14:04.089
[pause] And everyone who knows Jinnee will
tell you she can fly.

00:14:04.089 --> 00:14:12.209
But of all the very special things about Jinnee
perhaps what's most amazing about her is what

00:14:12.209 --> 00:14:17.120
she creates with her very magical wands.

00:14:17.120 --> 00:14:18.540
What are her wands?

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:20.610
Can you tell?

00:14:20.610 --> 00:14:21.610
They're her art materials.

00:14:21.610 --> 00:14:22.610
Right?

00:14:22.610 --> 00:14:24.920
That's how she creates her magic.

00:14:24.920 --> 00:14:28.810
With a few taps of a wand, Jinnee creates
animals.

00:14:28.810 --> 00:14:31.160
She can also make the seasons change.

00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:36.450
And conjure heroes and horses and people of
all sorts.

00:14:36.450 --> 00:14:41.130
And even a very good dinosaur.

00:14:41.130 --> 00:14:46.870
But for her sons Aristides and Michael, she
makes the most wonderful things of all.

00:14:46.870 --> 00:14:50.140
The things they love best.

00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:52.820
Big machines.

00:14:52.820 --> 00:14:57.370
[pause] It begins with a line.

00:14:57.370 --> 00:14:58.370
Black and rough.

00:14:58.370 --> 00:14:59.650
Then a squiggle.

00:14:59.650 --> 00:15:01.030
And a rub.

00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:04.579
As little Aristides watches, a puff of smoke
appears.

00:15:04.579 --> 00:15:05.579
Clears.

00:15:05.579 --> 00:15:08.019
And then, Woo!

00:15:08.019 --> 00:15:09.019
Woo!

00:15:09.019 --> 00:15:10.730
A whistle cries.

00:15:10.730 --> 00:15:11.980
Do more!

00:15:11.980 --> 00:15:14.610
Do more, Aristides shouts in return.

00:15:14.610 --> 00:15:16.320
So Jinnee draws and draws.

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:18.350
It's a train.

00:15:18.350 --> 00:15:19.770
I see a train, says Aristides.

00:15:19.770 --> 00:15:23.399
With each sweep Choo Choo comes more to life.

00:15:23.399 --> 00:15:26.920
She zips and zooms down the tracks.

00:15:26.920 --> 00:15:30.570
So Jinnee draws and draws.

00:15:30.570 --> 00:15:32.680
Choo Choo rings her bell.

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:38.190
And with Jinnee's magic, begins to tell the
story of the time that Choo Choo escaped.

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:45.100
To Aristides's delight, Choo Choo chugs off
to exciting, even dangerous adventures.

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:52.370
But, of course, in the end, she always comes
home safely.

00:15:52.370 --> 00:15:54.980
Michael loves watching big trucks hard at
work.

00:15:54.980 --> 00:15:55.980
Good job, John.

00:15:55.980 --> 00:15:56.980
[applause] Woo!

00:15:56.980 --> 00:15:57.980
Okay.

00:15:57.980 --> 00:15:58.980
Are we ready?

00:15:58.980 --> 00:15:59.980
&gt;&gt; John Rocco: I'm ready.

00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:03.180
&gt;&gt; Sherri Duskey Rinker: Okay.

00:16:03.180 --> 00:16:07.540
Now he is going to draw Mary Ann the steam
shovel.

00:16:07.540 --> 00:16:11.990
Michael loves watching big trucks hard at
work digging and building.

00:16:11.990 --> 00:16:13.570
Constantly moving.

00:16:13.570 --> 00:16:16.040
And so Jinnee watches trucks too.

00:16:16.040 --> 00:16:18.380
She observes patiently.

00:16:18.380 --> 00:16:19.920
Closely.

00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:21.100
And she begins.

00:16:21.100 --> 00:16:22.540
First, the lines.

00:16:22.540 --> 00:16:24.190
This time layered and sketchy.

00:16:24.190 --> 00:16:25.570
Then the circles.

00:16:25.570 --> 00:16:28.430
Then the brush bursts of red.

00:16:28.430 --> 00:16:29.700
A rumble.

00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:30.700
A power.

00:16:30.700 --> 00:16:31.740
Before dirt flies.

00:16:31.740 --> 00:16:38.180
And right before Michael's eyes, a bucket
loads and lifts clearing earth to make canals.

00:16:38.180 --> 00:16:39.920
Cutting through mountains for railways.

00:16:39.920 --> 00:16:42.560
Leveling land for highways and runways.

00:16:42.560 --> 00:16:45.930
Digging deep into the earth making foundations.

00:16:45.930 --> 00:16:48.490
Smoke blows from her stack.

00:16:48.490 --> 00:16:56.720
There loud and proud, strong and steely, always
hard at work Mary Ann.

00:16:56.720 --> 00:16:58.230
A steam shovel.

00:16:58.230 --> 00:17:00.019
Michael jumps with joy.

00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:07.610
Now Michael has a truck to call his very own
and Michael and Mary Ann smile at each other.

00:17:07.610 --> 00:17:10.110
Friends forever.

00:17:10.110 --> 00:17:14.370
And soon more big machines burst to life.

00:17:14.370 --> 00:17:16.530
First, there -- [inaudible speaker] Oh, okay.

00:17:16.530 --> 00:17:17.530
&gt;&gt; John Rocco: That's okay.

00:17:17.530 --> 00:17:18.530
&gt;&gt; Sherri Duskey Rinker: John's behind.

00:17:18.530 --> 00:17:20.780
Do you want me to keep going or do you want
me to slow down and sing something?

00:17:20.780 --> 00:17:22.360
&gt;&gt; John Rocco: No, I'll catch up.

00:17:22.360 --> 00:17:23.670
&gt;&gt; Sherri Duskey Rinker: Oh, okay.

00:17:23.670 --> 00:17:26.600
And soon more big machines burst to life.

00:17:26.600 --> 00:17:28.470
First, there's just paper.

00:17:28.470 --> 00:17:29.470
White.

00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:30.470
White.

00:17:30.470 --> 00:17:31.470
White.

00:17:31.470 --> 00:17:32.470
Jinnee touches it.

00:17:32.470 --> 00:17:33.470
And pop.

00:17:33.470 --> 00:17:34.470
With a whoosh of black.

00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:36.630
Some strokes of red and green.

00:17:36.630 --> 00:17:39.590
Aristides and Michael meet Katy.

00:17:39.590 --> 00:17:42.830
Katy is a beautiful bright crawler tractor.

00:17:42.830 --> 00:17:45.230
She can roll on her thick, black treads.

00:17:45.230 --> 00:17:50.740
She can plow with a bulldozer blade -- she
can push with a bulldozer blade attached.

00:17:50.740 --> 00:17:55.470
But best of all Katy can plow.

00:17:55.470 --> 00:18:00.120
The city of Geopolis is buried in a giant
winter storm and the people are counting on

00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:01.120
Katy.

00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:04.530
She's the only one big and strong enough to
clear the way.

00:18:04.530 --> 00:18:09.840
Katy is rough, tough, and ready to plow the
miles and piles of snow.

00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.500
No amount of snow can stop her.

00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:15.250
Follow me she says as she revs.

00:18:15.250 --> 00:18:22.590
And with a "chug, chug, chug," Katy is off
to dig out the town of Geopolis while Aristides

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:25.919
and Michael cheer her on.

00:18:25.919 --> 00:18:28.660
^M00:18:26 Jinnee makes more lines.

00:18:28.660 --> 00:18:32.170
This time wavy and curvy, swoopy and swervy.

00:18:32.170 --> 00:18:35.670
Like music lines flow along.

00:18:35.670 --> 00:18:39.700
Color joins in free and watery.

00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:48.440
[Background music] And soon -- [laughter]
"Ting, ting, ting."

00:18:48.440 --> 00:18:55.190
There is Maybelle the cable car climbing up
and down the giant hills of San Francisco.

00:18:55.190 --> 00:18:56.600
Our day is not done.

00:18:56.600 --> 00:19:02.310
It's just begun she sings while Aristides
and Michael wave "clingity, cling."

00:19:02.310 --> 00:19:07.790
Maybelle rolls away to do the job she loves.

00:19:07.790 --> 00:19:10.380
And there's a picture of Jinnee with the actual
Maybelle.

00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:12.000
We have five minutes, John.

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:13.200
Keep drawing.

00:19:13.200 --> 00:19:15.440
Next, Jinnee makes a little house.

00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:20.830
Pink and smiling surrounded by apple trees
on a hill covered with daisies.

00:19:20.830 --> 00:19:26.610
That doesn't seem like our kind of story,
say the boys pouting.

00:19:26.610 --> 00:19:31.120
Don't worry, says Jinnee as she keeps working.

00:19:31.120 --> 00:19:34.920
Suddenly before their eyes, Mary Ann is there.

00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:37.210
Then cars appear racing along.

00:19:37.210 --> 00:19:38.620
Tractor and trolley cars.

00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:44.809
And there a tow truck pulls a car with a flat.

00:19:44.809 --> 00:19:46.300
Trains and buses.

00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:47.540
Even a subway.

00:19:47.540 --> 00:19:54.940
Big construction vehicles roll in smoky and
strong hauling heavy loads.

00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:56.350
Jinnee draws and draws.

00:19:56.350 --> 00:19:57.350
Roads.

00:19:57.350 --> 00:19:58.350
Buildings.

00:19:58.350 --> 00:19:59.350
Traffic.

00:19:59.350 --> 00:20:00.510
People all in a hurry.

00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:01.919
It's much too much.

00:20:01.919 --> 00:20:03.330
Skies darken.

00:20:03.330 --> 00:20:05.289
The little house sags.

00:20:05.289 --> 00:20:09.230
And Aristides and Michael are worried.

00:20:09.230 --> 00:20:14.520
And then just like that the little pink house
is saved by a truck.

00:20:14.520 --> 00:20:15.520
The boys jump up.

00:20:15.520 --> 00:20:16.520
That truck is a hero.

00:20:16.520 --> 00:20:18.920
The truck saved the day.

00:20:18.920 --> 00:20:20.270
Jinnee smiles to herself.

00:20:20.270 --> 00:20:23.690
Well, of course, they see it that way.

00:20:23.690 --> 00:20:28.890
Choo Choo and Mary Ann, Katy, Maybelle, and
all of the trucks around the little house

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:38.260
big, powerful heroes, hard working, and happy
and each special and wonderful.

00:20:38.260 --> 00:20:40.789
Just like Jinnee.

00:20:40.789 --> 00:20:48.150
And that is how here in Folley Cove Jinnee's
big machines and their stories come to life

00:20:48.150 --> 00:20:52.590
quite magically.

00:20:52.590 --> 00:20:57.030
For Aristides and Michael.

00:20:57.030 --> 00:20:58.340
And for you.

