00:21:12.830 --> 00:21:16.429
us at our signing line so, please, do come
over.

00:21:16.429 --> 00:21:17.429
And -- is there anything else?

00:21:17.429 --> 00:21:18.429
&gt;&gt; John Rocco: Yeah.

00:21:18.429 --> 00:21:25.400
I just wanted to ask you Sherri, when you
thought about writing this book, as a children's

00:21:25.400 --> 00:21:31.470
book author-illustrator, what possessed you
to write a book about Virginia Lee Burton?

00:21:31.470 --> 00:21:36.289
&gt;&gt; Sherri Duskey Rinker: When I was growing
up, Jinnee Burton was my favorite children's

00:21:36.289 --> 00:21:37.289
book author.

00:21:37.289 --> 00:21:38.289
I grew up with "The Little House."

00:21:38.289 --> 00:21:40.280
It was the first story I remember writing
-- reading.

00:21:40.280 --> 00:21:42.510
It was a story my grandma read to me.

00:21:42.510 --> 00:21:46.750
And when I became a children's book author,
it was my dream to write a story that would

00:21:46.750 --> 00:21:52.919
somehow pay tribute to this amazing woman
who was so far ahead of her time.

00:21:52.919 --> 00:21:54.230
She ran a business.

00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:56.370
She raised children.

00:21:56.370 --> 00:21:57.940
She grew for her garden.

00:21:57.940 --> 00:22:01.080
She canned and cooked and had parties.

00:22:01.080 --> 00:22:02.160
And taught.

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:05.220
And I think she inspired me.

00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:10.309
The more that I read about her, the more that
I researched I was inspired to tell everyone

00:22:10.309 --> 00:22:16.780
that the world should know what an incredible,
creative talent she was and how much ahead

00:22:16.780 --> 00:22:19.330
of her time that she was.

00:22:19.330 --> 00:22:24.520
She was born in 1909 and lived the biggest
part of her life during the depression and

00:22:24.520 --> 00:22:30.250
the years immediately following when she was
raising kids and did so much with so little.

00:22:30.250 --> 00:22:36.200
So I hope that you guys learned a little bit
about her and that maybe, maybe, maybe you

00:22:36.200 --> 00:22:39.330
are starting to love her just as much as I
do.

00:22:39.330 --> 00:22:41.400
So thank you so much for coming.

00:22:41.400 --> 00:22:42.520
[applause] Oh.

00:22:42.520 --> 00:22:43.760
And can we give those away, John?

00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:44.760
&gt;&gt; John Rocco: Sure.

00:22:44.760 --> 00:22:45.760
&gt;&gt; Sherri Duskey Rinker: Okay.

00:22:45.760 --> 00:22:46.760
We're going to give John's drawings away.

00:22:46.760 --> 00:22:47.760
Is that okay?

00:22:47.760 --> 00:22:48.910
[applause] Two?

